Maximum length of shells of
N . verbernei
from Brazil were very similar to Caribbean ones, reaching 3.66 mm and eight teleoconch whorls in the present study, but 3.50 mm (
Rolán & Fernández-Garcés 2007
) or 3.20 mm (
Moolenbeek & Faber 1989
) and seven teleoconch whorls in the Caribbean. Such dimensions make
N . verbernei
one of the smallest species of Triphoridae in the western Atlantic.

